[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Hello everyone. I am [music] Freya, solution manager at Excite. If you\'re working in reality capture, &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; the following probably hits home. You scan all day, get back to your desk, open the file, [music] and the points are patchy, the floors are tilted, and the edges are mush,'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'unusable. [music] Sometimes you even have to head back out and re-scan everything. What you really need is point cloud data that\'s accurate, [music] structurally precise, true in color, and properly leveled. That\'s the bar we set'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for Xeo [music] Studio 4.0. Our algorithm upgrades serve one goal, engineering grade data you can trust. Enough talk, let\'s look at the results. &gt;&gt; [music]'

[00:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; First up, coloring. The new algorithm'

[01:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'delivers photorealistic point [music] cloud color, vivid, even true to what you saw on site. Low light isn\'t a problem either. Basements, parking garages, places where structural detail'

[01:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'used to vanish into [music] the dark can now be replicated clearly. Paired with our Xeo upsample algorithm, and the detail scope goes even further. Check this out. Have you ever scanned a QR'

[01:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'code from a point cloud? That\'s the level of detail we\'re talking about. So, when [music] you\'re tracing point clouds to draw floor plans or elevations, accurate color makes materials and boundaries obvious at a glance.'

[01:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; No guesswork, just draw. Next, leveling. Anyone who\'s drafted interior plans knows this pain. If your base [music] plan is even slightly off. Everything downstream falls apart. Walls, floors,'

[01:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ceiling [music] heights, all corrected one by one and by hand. Slow, tedious, and completely avoidable. With 4.0, horizontal [music] stays horizontal, vertical stays vertical. Watch that'

[02:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'horizontal slice cutting down layer by layer. The leveling improvement is right there [music] in front of you. And here\'s a 24-story building captured with Autopole, plumb top to bottom, minimal drift. To turn this on, just'

[02:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'toggle high precision [music] optimization in your processing settings. Right now, it\'s tuned for indoor structures things processed with relative coordinates. Next up, filtering. There\'s a common issue in'

[02:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'point cloud processing today, and [music] it\'s not that filters are too weak, but too aggressive. You\'ve seen this. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; The noise is gone, but the railing went with it. The filter can\'t tell which [music] is which. Our approach is AI'

[02:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'filtering. We strip out noise and trailing artifacts while preserving [music] the structural detail. For trickier things like utility corridors and railings, [music] we build dedicated filters that targets the trailing noise'

[03:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'between the structure without touching the structures themselves. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; What you get is a clean point cloud, easier to measure and to draft. And clean input means clean output, which takes [music] us straight to mesh. Mesh'

[03:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in 4.0 improves on two fronts. On structure, better noise [music] resistance, fewer holes, much less thickening. Fine details that used to clump into a blur now separate with sharp outlines. On texture, [music] the'

[03:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'coloring upgrade I mentioned earlier feeds straight into mesh texture mapping. Cleaner, sharper, closer to life. On top of the [music] algorithm work, we\'ve also overhauled the user interface. The tools you reach for every'

[03:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'day. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; 3D clipping, slicing, measurement, all rebuilt to be faster and more intuitive. Less clicking, less guessing, more time doing actual [music] work. We put everything 4.0 brings to the best across'

[03:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'real world scenarios. Engineering grade data ready to use the moment processing finishes. That\'s Lexo Studio 4.0. Head to xrite.com to download and try it and'

[04:07] [scene:talk]
